CONFIGURATION PROCEDURE

* Install Kismet in a remote host: /etc/kismet/kismet.conf

logexpiry=3600
logtemplate=/var/log/kismet/%n_%D-%i.%l
configdir=/var/lib/kismet/

* Launch kismet_server in remote host:

/usr/bin/kismet_server -l xml -t REMOTEHOSTIP -f /etc/kismet/kismet.conf
/2>&1 | logger -t REMOTEHOSTIP  -p local7.1

* Configure rsyslog in remote host: /etc/rsyslog.conf
*.*                             @LOCALHOSTIP

* In a local OSSIM ossim host: 

mkdir -p /var/ossim/kismet/work
mkdir -p /var/ossim/kismet/parsed

* Create /etc/cron.hourly/kismet adding: 

#!/bin/bash
/usr/bin/perl /usr/share/ossim/www/wireless/fetch_kismet.pl

* Remote host need ssh root public key into authorized_host: 
In local host:
ssh-keygen -t rsa
scp id_rsa.pub REMOTE_IP:/root
ssh REMOTE_IP
cat id_rsa.pub >> .ssh/authorized_keys

* Edit /usr/share/ossim/www/wireless/fetch_kismet.pl and edit %site hash:
$sites{'REMOTE_IP'}='/var/log/kismet';  # Kismet log files location path

* Launch /etc/cron.daily/kismet and then go to
SIEM->Detection->Wireless IDS and configure a Location adding available
kismet sensors.

